listing.name: Burn Down the List
listing.description:
This Power-Up integrates directly with Trello to improve visibility on project progress. This in turn leads to more timely adjustments, and more projects delivered on schedule.

## Feature Overview
![This project is two days behind ideal schedule](https://bdtl.burndown-analytics.com/bdtl-card.png)
As project tasks are completed, they are moved into the burn down list to be counted toward overall project completion.
The project will have a burn down chart updated in real time, right at the top of the burn down list. 

![Hovering shows chart values.](https://bdtl.burndown-analytics.com/bdtl-card-back.png)
The burn down chart is attached to the front of the burn down card for maximum visibility, and the back of the card contains an interactive version of the chart.

## Getting Started
To get started, add the Power-Up and then select Burn Down the List from the list action menu.
![Select the Burn Down the List action.](https://bdtl.burndown-analytics.com/list-action-anim.gif)

A configuration menu for the initial burn down chart will allow you to set the project duration and expected point count.
The duration can be changed at any time by modifying the card due date, and the expected point count can be changed by updating the number in the list name.
![Configure initial chart parameters.](https://bdtl.burndown-analytics.com/initial-config.png)

Points for the project estimate or for completed task cards can be specified by including any number in the name, optionally surrounded by braces. For example the following names all indicate a project or task card with 200 estimated points:

 - "My Big Project (200)"
 - "My Big 200 Point Project" 
 - "{200} Paint the shed"
 - "(200) Mow the lawn"

As completed cards are moved into the burn down list, the chart will update with the new point count for the day. Completed cards need a point count in their title, as well as a due date that is marked complete.

![A 5 point card is brought into the list and the points remaining count for the day is reduced by 5.](https://bdtl.burndown-analytics.com/card-completion.gif)

## Pricing
After a free 5-day trial, $6.85 per month enables unlimited burn down lists across an unlimited number of boards for the entire team.

## Questions
Please email bdtl@burndown-analytics.com and we'll answer any questions you may have.

----

listing.name: Agile Guy
listing.description:
Agile Guy will help you manage and track your agile sprint!  

# What can you do with Agile Guy? 
_Nearly all Except coffee..._

## Organize your board
You can display if you want, the ID of the card. Moreover, you can prioritize and reorder them by this priority :)
You can block a card if you have an issue and easily see it on the board
![organize](https://www.faq.agileguy.me/assets/estimation.png)
![points on a card](https://www.faq.agileguy.me/assets/2.png)

## Build a sprint
You can create a Sprint and estimate cards in Story points. Then, you can see the *burndown chart* of this sprint and follow the big picture of the sprint 
![report](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/sprint.png)
![report](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/graph.png)

## Be alerted of WIP limit
In fact, you can create an alert if too many cards are in the selected columns. It can help you to maintain rules on your board captain!
![alert](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/gif3.gif)

## Bug Tracking 
Yes, you can track on a period, the evolution of created and fixed bugs :) 
![bug](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/1.png)
![tracker](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/3.png)

## See the time since the last activity
Yes, sir! You can do that if you want to see the old cards which don't move

## Report
Analyze your sprint thanks to the report with the number of points done, the cards blocked during the sprint and the cards done!
![sprint](https://www.app.agileguy.me/asset/report.png)
## Plan
You have two weeks to test and then it's 10$ per year ;) 

## More informations? 
[Visit our FAQ](https://faq.agileguy.me/faq.html)

listing.name: Agile Dashboards by Corrello
listing.description:
Burndowns, Burnup, Cycle time, CFD, Slow Cards, custom stats, Agile Metrics and more...

*"This is a *really* nice product. I'm really happy with what you've built here. It's everything I need in a Scrum/Kanban tool and nothing I don't. Blows JIRA completely out of the water."*
- Scott McCoy (Software Engineer at **OpenX**)


The [Corrello](https://getcorrello.com?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=plugin) Power-Up for Trello instantly and seamlessly integrates with Trello giving you the charts you need in seconds. So while your team can continue using the tool they love, you can get the charts and reports you need to properly manage an agile project. With Corrello’s **burndown**, **burnup**, **CFD** and **Cycle Time** charts you have the everything you need to show your team how they are working and help them identify the bottlenecks where they can improve. Corrello also helps with reporting outside the team, adding some data and rigour when explaining estimates to stakeholders outside the team.

* **Identify and communicate bottlenecks** to your team with the Cumulative flow diagram and Cycle time stats. Cycle Times are also shown on the back of completed Cards in Trello.
* **Manage Sprint progress** and stay on schedule with the Sprint Burndown chart.
* **Keep your whole project on schedule** and communicate progress with the Release burnup.
* Keep on top of what’s happening over time with historical **counts of bugs**, **velocity** and work in progress, etc.
* See **Slow Cards** which you can get moving today, with Age in List and Age in Progress shown directly on your Trello Cards
* Add a new level of data and rigour to reporting estimates and team progress in your projects.

Access your charts and Corrello dashboards from the link in the top right of your board after installing this Power-Up.

Some of our happy customers
-----*"**Corrello has transformed Trello from a delightful way to organize work into a powerful agile project management tool.** With Corrello's seamlessly integrated charts and analysis we can easily track the progress of all of our teams and projects. If you are using Trello to manage any Scrum, Kanban or other agile process, **get Corrello now. You are flying blind without it**."*
- Chris Brookins (CPO **HelpScout**)

*"We use Trello at Pusher because it's so simple to use, and it's the nearest thing to a physical task board. **Corrello gives us actionable data we use to effectively manage our development process**, without the team needing to do anything new and without any changes needed to their workflow."*
- Sam Stagg (VP Eng **Pusher**)


*"The best agile tool for Trello"*
- Anita Taylor (PM **Stack Overflow**) 

![Scrum team Burndown](https://getcorrello.com/public/images/powerup/burndown.png)
![Kanban team CFD Cumulative Flow Diagram](https://getcorrello.com/public/images/powerup/cfd.png)
![Cycletime chart for Kanban](https://getcorrello.com/public/images/powerup/cycle_time.png)
![Custom stats](https://getcorrello.com/public/images/powerup/stats.png)
 

Corrello is ideal for both Scrum and Kanban teams, or those teams working with a mix of both Scrum and Kanban.

Scrum team features

- Burndown charts and historical burndowns in Corrello
- Burndown chart plus current sprint progress emailed every day
- Access burndown charts and stats in Slack

Kanban team features

- Cumulative Flow Diagrams (CFDs)
- Cycle Time
- Daily email with latest WIP, recent changes and Slow Cards

Common features for all Agile teams

- Release burnup - forecast when you will be done
- Slow cards - see work which is stuck in progress
- Retrospective emails showing recent data from your dashboards

listing.name: Calendar
listing.description:
Bring perspective to due dates with the Calendar Power-Up for Trello. Whether you are planning a conference, managing an editorial calendar, or organizing a family vacation, the Calendar Power-Up let’s you display cards with due dates in a weekly or monthly calendar view. Easily prioritize cards by dragging and dropping them on the calendar to automatically update their due dates, and export your Trello calendar to third party apps with an iCalendar link.

- Display and filter cards with due dates in a weekly or monthly calendar view.

- Manage due dates by dragging and dropping cards on the calendar.

- Easily see completed tasks by marking due dates complete.

- Export a board’s calendar to third party calendars with each board’s unique iCalendar link.

- The Calendar Power-Up is supported on the web and iOS and Android mobile devices.

![screenshot](https://calendar.trello.services/images/Calendar_1.jpg)
![screenshot](https://calendar.trello.services/images/Calendar_2.jpg)
![screenshot](https://calendar.trello.services/images/Calendar_3.jpg)
![screenshot](https://calendar.trello.services/images/Calendar_4.jpg)
